                </FooterDetails>
                <MainParagraph>On January 25, 1993, President William J. Clinton
                                    signed Executive Order 12835 to establish the National Economic
                                    Council (NEC). The NEC coordinates the economic policymaking
                                    process and advises the President on economic policy. The NEC
                                    also ensures that economic policy decisions and programs remain
                                    consistent with the President's stated goals, and it monitors
                                    the implementation of the President's economic
                                    goals.</MainParagraph>
