                <Header>History</Header>
                <Paragraph>The William J. Clinton Presidential Library posted video footage of President Clinton signing  Executive Order 12835 and giving remarks on the establishment of the NEC. The signing and the remarks took place on on January 25, 1993. The President singled out the efforts of Robert E. Rubin, who served as the NEC's first Director after leaving the Goldman Sachs Group, Inc., in 1992.</Paragraph>
